This paper deals with evaluating the effectiveness of security products in detecting zero-day malware, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also proposes a time-delay method for collecting labeled samples, which involves the use of machine learning algorithms (cs.AI) and statistical analysis (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the challenges involved in accurately labeling samples, which is a common issue in software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper addresses the issue of modeling the heterogeneous distribution of files on various networks, which falls under the category of network and internet architecture (cs.NI).
